A simple and modern GTK eBook viewer, built with GJS and Epub.js


Supported formats:
EPUB (.epub, .epub3)
Kindle (.azw, .azw3) and Mobipocket (.mobi)
FictionBook (.fb2, .fb2.zip)
Comic book archive (.cbr, .cbz, .cbt, .cb7)
Plain text (.txt)

Single-column, two-column, or continuous scrolling layouts
Adjust font, line-spacing, and margins
Customize colors and brightness
Reading progress slider with chapter marks
Bookmarks and annotations
Find in book
Open footnotes in popovers
Touchpad gesturesâ€”use two-finger swipe to turn the page
Quick dictionary lookup with 
- Wiktionary
- Wikipedia
- dictd
- sdcv
- translate text with Google Translate

Basic text-to-speech support with eSpeak NG and Festival

Optional dependencies : 

On SBo
- libhandy : is recommended to make the interface
  work better on larger as well as smaller screens
- gspell : for spellchecking notes
- tracker : can be used to track the locations of files
- dictd or sdcv : to use offline dictionaries

Non-SBo
- festival or espeak-ng : text-to-speech support
